-- Argentine Stocks: Banco Macro, Grupo Galicia Gain After Earnings
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-02-16T18:23:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-16/argentine-stocks-banco-macro-grupo-galicia-gain-after-earnings.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 3:08 p.m. in  Buenos
Aires .  The  Merval (MERVAL)  Index rose 1.3 percent to 2,760.38.  Banco Macro SA (BMA)  (BMA AF),  Argentina ’s largest lender by
market share, advanced 2.9 percent to 10.60 pesos after saying
fourth-quarter net income climbed 26 percent from a year earlier
to 346.4 million pesos ($79.6 million). The company’s  American
depositary receipts were upgraded to “overweight” from
“neutral” at JPMorgan Chase & Co., which cited “continued
good loan growth, an expansion in financial margins, and solid
fee growth.”  Grupo Financiero Galicia SA (GGAL)  , Argentina’s largest
consumer lender, increased 2.6 percent to 3.50 pesos. Grupo
Galicia climbed for a second day after reporting 2011 earnings
per share increased to 0.892 centavos from 0.329 the prior year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
